Josh,<br><br>
I did not accuse Cook or MTF of being racist. I said that what they said was racist /  anti-semetic ... There is a difference. We all have elements of Racism, anti-what-ever- ism in us. At times this comes out. It is important to call people on their transgressions, but not to judge them in  based on a statement or two.  There is a big differnece!<br><br>
One can lead to discussion, the other to the types of arguments that I know so well from the anti-war movement.<br><br>
Further.. I don't care how cook got ordained. What matters here is what he says, period. I would appreciate your identifying yourself as we all have done. I have put out my sometimes less than popular opinions and have recieved no hate mail. If you put your address down, maybe you would be more considerate of how you state your opinions.<br><br>
John... I agree with you about Clinton's administration. If what we hear about Clinton is true ( or if 1/3 of it is true) his personal actions are an embarrassment. As were those of most of the past presidents in the last 40 years. I do think that he was tried to accomplish much on the world front without resorting to military action, and I agree with this.<br><br>
Cook.. Leave off that I nominated you for President from your resume. Just state that you were nominated. We can have this uncovered as a scandal in your administration. Then I can be famous too!<br><br>
MTF..  You left out loud mouthed anti-war protesters who have been known to speak before thinking.. Was that an accident?? :-)
